Whitewater first appeared as a [[census-designated place]] in the [[2010 U.S. census]].<ref name=2010CensusCA/>

The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Whitewater had a population of 984. The population density was {{convert|99.6|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup was 405 (41.2%) [[White Americans|White]], 56 (5.7%) [[African Americans|African American]], 23 (2.3%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 18 (1.8%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 7 (0.7%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 303 (30.8%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 172 (17.5%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 540 persons (54.9%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Whitewater CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0685208 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=July 14, 2025}}</ref>

The census reported that 969 people (98.5% of the population) lived in households, 3 (0.3%) lived in non-institutionalized group quarters, and 12 (1.2%) were institutionalized.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 334 households, out of which 103 (30.8%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 136 (40.7%) were married-couple households, 37 (11.1%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 91 (27.2%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 70 (21.0%) had a male householder with no partner present. 71 households (21.3%) were one person, and 26 (7.8%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.9.<ref name=DP1/> There were 230 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (68.9% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Whitewater CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0685208 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=July 14, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 213 people (21.6%) under the age of 18, 93 people (9.5%) aged 18 to 24, 263 people (26.7%) aged 25 to 44, 281 people (28.6%) aged 45 to 64, and 134 people (13.6%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 39.0{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 97.2 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 392 housing units at an average density of {{convert|39.7|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 334 (85.2%) were occupied. Of these, 247 (74.0%) were owner-occupied, and 87 (26.0%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

